  "name": "Triton Capture by Neptune",
  "description": "Initial conditions from Agnor & Hamilton (2006, Nature 441, 192–194): an equal-mass Triton binary on a planar encounter with v∞ = 0.50 km s⁻¹, q_e = 8 R_N, and a_B = 20 R₁ (ρ₁ = 2.0 g cm⁻³). The encounter is set up in a Neptune-centered frame, as in the paper's Figure 1 — the Sun is included for context at ~30 AU. A binary orbital phase that yields exchange capture is used. At default playback speed, capture begins after roughly 45–60 seconds of simulation time, and Triton remains bound to Neptune.",
